253
00:30:03.387 --> 00:30:06.765
They need to mark the lines now!
We have no lines!

254
00:30:06.807 --> 00:30:10.060
We have enemies and friendlies
mixed in all over the place.

255
00:30:10.143 --> 00:30:12.104
Sir. our perimeter is collapsing.

256
00:30:12.187 --> 00:30:14.439
Alpha Company and Bravo Company
cannot hold.

257
00:30:14.481 --> 00:30:16.441
Charlie Company is being overrun.

258
00:30:19.236 --> 00:30:21.363
Net call! Net call!

259
00:30:21.446 --> 00:30:23.365
Keep this net clear!

260
00:30:39.256 --> 00:30:40.716
Hastings!

261
00:30:44.845 --> 00:30:46.388
Broken arrow!

262
00:30:49.057 --> 00:30:51.226
Broken arrow!

263
00:30:51.310 --> 00:30:54.396
I say again!
Broken arrow!

264
00:30:54.479 --> 00:30:56.565
We have br.oken ar.r.ow!

265
00:30:56.648 --> 00:30:58.150
Confirm. Broken arrow.

266
00:30:58.192 --> 00:31:00.110
Broken arrow confirmed.

267
00:31:00.152 --> 00:31:01.320
Broken arrow?

268
00:31:01.361 --> 00:31:03.488
That means that an American unit
has been overrun.

269
00:31:03.530 --> 00:31:06.325
It calls in every combat aircraft
for support.

270
00:31:06.366 --> 00:31:09.494
My God. there's no hiding it now.

271
00:31:30.807 --> 00:31:33.519
Charlie Company. report!
Signal is out!

272
00:31:33.519 --> 00:31:35.729
Bravo Company. report!

273
00:31:35.812 --> 00:31:39.775
Roger that!
Planes are on their way. Colonel!

274
00:31:40.609 --> 00:31:41.735
Sir!

275
00:31:45.739 --> 00:31:47.199
Roger that!

276
00:31:58.293 --> 00:32:00.712
We have planes
at every 1.000 feet...

277
00:32:00.754 --> 00:32:03.799
from 7.000 to 35.000...
we'll get 'em. sir!

278
00:32:05.884 --> 00:32:09.263
Advancing north
on our position at 1 -5-0.

279
00:32:27.406 --> 00:32:29.658
Nine-six-two-five-zero-seven--

280
00:32:37.082 --> 00:32:39.960
They're getting closer in
on 3-1 -5 degrees!

281
00:32:40.002 --> 00:32:43.839
Tha�s 0-5-0!
Repeat. 0-5-0!

282
00:32:50.012 --> 00:32:51.388
Goddamn it.

283
00:33:03.066 --> 00:33:07.154
Company sighted out in the open.
advancing north on our position.

284
00:33:07.237 --> 00:33:10.532
They're advancing on
3-1 -5 degrees at 1 -5-0.

285
00:33:12.159 --> 00:33:15.704
Bring it closer in
on 3-1 -5 degrees at 0-5-0...

286
00:33:15.787 --> 00:33:18.790
Charlie. call that
son of a bitch off!

287
00:33:18.832 --> 00:33:20.834
Call an abort now!

288
00:33:20.918 --> 00:33:21.835
Pull up!

289
00:33:24.129 --> 00:33:25.881
Get down!

290
00:33:52.991 --> 00:33:55.702
Charlie. listen to me.
You're keeping us alive now.

291
00:33:55.786 --> 00:33:58.705
You forget about that one
and you keep 'em coming in.

292
00:33:58.789 --> 00:34:00.374
You're doing well. son.

293
00:34:02.835 --> 00:34:04.837
Seven-oh-two...

294
00:34:04.878 --> 00:34:06.880
Attack against the tree line.

295
00:34:17.808 --> 00:34:20.477
Medic! Medic!

296
00:34:35.158 --> 00:34:38.287
Oh. God! Jimmy.
You know this guy?

297
00:34:38.328 --> 00:34:40.497
You know him? Talk to him.
Just talk to him!

298
00:34:41.331 --> 00:34:43.292
Jimmy. do you hear me?

299
00:34:43.375 --> 00:34:45.544
I�s Joe.
I�s Joe Galloway.

300
00:34:45.627 --> 00:34:48.964
Doc's giving you morphine.
We're gonna get you out of here.

301
00:34:55.596 --> 00:34:58.599
We gotta get him to
the landing zone. Grab his legs!

302
00:35:10.861 --> 00:35:13.697
You gotta get him out of here.
Hey! Hey!

303
00:35:13.739 --> 00:35:16.700
I can't help you!
You gotta do it by yourself!

304
00:35:16.783 --> 00:35:19.328
Get him on that chopper. okay?
Yes. sir.

305
00:36:18.345 --> 00:36:20.722
Tell my wife I love her...

306
00:36:20.806 --> 00:36:22.891
and my baby!

307
00:36:22.975 --> 00:36:25.435
You tell'em!

308
00:37:51.438 --> 00:37:53.065
Captain Nadal.
Sir...

309
00:37:53.148 --> 00:37:55.692
Now that we put 'em back on
their heels. we got us a lull.

310
00:37:55.776 --> 00:37:57.110
I want you to attack.

311
00:37:57.194 --> 00:37:59.947
I want you to go overthere
and rescue that cut off platoon.

312
00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:03.116
Yes. sir!
First Squad. move out!

313
00:38:04.785 --> 00:38:07.037
Come on. guys.
Move it!

314
00:38:11.291 --> 00:38:12.584
Add fifty.

315
00:38:13.210 --> 00:38:15.212
Keep moving the artillery forward!

316
00:38:15.295 --> 00:38:17.631
Keep walking the artillery forward!

317
00:38:17.714 --> 00:38:18.799
Spread it out!

318
00:38:22.719 --> 00:38:24.847
Move it!

319
00:38:27.307 --> 00:38:30.102
Move it!
Keep moving forward!

320
00:38:46.034 --> 00:38:48.537
Sergeant Savage.
you guys still here?

321
00:39:07.014 --> 00:39:09.683
We have 40 KIA.
we have two MIA.

322
00:39:09.766 --> 00:39:11.685
These are the latest numbers.
Over.

323
00:39:41.507 --> 00:39:45.135
Tha�s a nice day.
Sergeant Savage.

324
00:39:53.143 --> 00:39:56.188
Forty dead.
two unaccounted for. sir.

325
00:39:56.271 --> 00:39:58.106
Right.

326
00:39:58.982 --> 00:40:01.860
All right. boys.
le�s get 'em up and get 'em out.

327
00:40:10.661 --> 00:40:13.580
Le�s get 'em out of here
and get 'em on the chopper!

328
00:40:16.583 --> 00:40:19.294
Since most of the men
being loaded on the chopper...

329
00:40:19.378 --> 00:40:20.754
are from Charlie Company...

330
00:40:20.796 --> 00:40:22.339
I want you to take their place.

331
00:40:22.422 --> 00:40:26.134
I'll show you where. Follow me.
Yes. sir! Le�s go!

332
00:41:23.984 --> 00:41:26.528
Captain. have your men dig
some firing steps.

333
00:41:26.612 --> 00:41:28.780
Throw some dirt on those bodies.
keep the smell down.

334
00:41:28.864 --> 00:41:30.741
Roger. Sergeant Major.

335
00:41:30.824 --> 00:41:34.953
Kind of makes you wish you'd
signed up for submarines. don't it?

336
00:41:35.037 --> 00:41:39.541
Brigade headquarters wants you out
on the first chopper at dawn.

337
00:41:39.625 --> 00:41:43.253
What idiot would keep ordering that
in the middle of a goddamn battle?

338
00:41:43.295 --> 00:41:46.298
Gen. Westmoreland wants a briefing.
Give me the horn.

339
00:41:47.090 --> 00:41:48.842
I am in a fight...

340
00:41:48.926 --> 00:41:51.845
and I object to this order
to return to Saigon.

341
00:41:51.929 --> 00:41:54.097
Now. I will not leave my men.

342
00:41:54.139 --> 00:41:56.141
Is that clear?
Out.

343
00:42:03.732 --> 00:42:05.651
There's two of my men
unaccounted for out there...

344
00:42:05.734 --> 00:42:07.653
and i�s where
the worst of the fighting was...

345
00:42:07.736 --> 00:42:09.530
so they'll be out there someplace.

346
00:42:09.613 --> 00:42:12.407
Le�s go out and get 'em.
I'm with you. sir.

347
00:42:12.449 --> 00:42:13.951
All right.

348
00:42:14.034 --> 00:42:15.536
Le�s go.

349
00:44:08.690 --> 00:44:10.651
They...

350
00:44:10.734 --> 00:44:12.402
brought another...

351
00:44:12.486 --> 00:44:14.571
Oh. God.
Julie. i�s yours.

352
00:45:02.703 --> 00:45:05.038
He died keeping my promise.

353
00:45:36.069 --> 00:45:38.030
Sir. they're ordering us all out.

354
00:45:38.113 --> 00:45:40.490
All of us.

355
00:45:40.532 --> 00:45:42.910
They're gonna march reinforcements in.

356
00:45:42.951 --> 00:45:45.454
They don't understand a damn thing. do they?

357
00:45:46.246 --> 00:45:47.789
Can't get out.

358
00:45:50.792 --> 00:45:53.212
He's waiting up there in a cave.
and tha�s what he wants.

359
00:45:53.295 --> 00:45:55.464
The minute he sees live soldiers
hopping on a helicopter...

360
00:45:55.547 --> 00:45:58.383
he'll be all over us
and then he'll get what he wants.

361
00:45:58.425 --> 00:46:00.719
He'll get his massacre.

362
00:46:09.311 --> 00:46:11.980
Requesting permission
to rejoin the lines. sir.

363
00:46:15.734 --> 00:46:17.444
All right. son.

364
00:46:21.532 --> 00:46:23.575
Garry Owen. sir.

365
00:46:46.181 --> 00:46:48.934
I wonder what was going through
Custer's mind when he realized...

366
00:46:49.017 --> 00:46:51.311
he'd led his men into a slaughter.

367
00:46:52.980 --> 00:46:55.732
Sir. Custer was a pussy.

368
00:46:57.734 --> 00:46:59.486
You ain't.

369
00:47:02.364 --> 00:47:03.991
Goddamn.

370
00:47:09.079 --> 00:47:10.539
Hell.

371
00:47:14.042 --> 00:47:16.211
Right now they're planning
their final attack...

372
00:47:16.295 --> 00:47:18.380
the one that will finish us off.

373
00:47:19.256 --> 00:47:21.717
They'll nibble at us all night.
then...

374
00:47:21.758 --> 00:47:24.803
come dawn they'll hit us
with everything they got.

375
00:47:26.346 --> 00:47:28.932
Tha�s what I'd do if I was him.

376
00:47:33.979 --> 00:47:37.608
Sergeant Major. hand out
the last of the ammunition.

377
00:47:37.691 --> 00:47:39.610
Yes. sir.

378
00:49:00.482 --> 00:49:01.900
Fix bayonets.

379
00:53:19.658 --> 00:53:22.202
You were wondering
how Custer felt. sir.

380
00:53:23.829 --> 00:53:25.414
You ought to ask him.

381
00:55:44.178 --> 00:55:45.762
Sergeant Savage!

382
00:55:54.438 --> 00:55:56.732
Checking the dead enemies
for documents...

383
00:55:56.815 --> 00:55:59.359
and I found this on the guy
that tried to bayonet you.

384
00:55:59.401 --> 00:56:02.029
Translated some of it.
mostly personal.

385
00:56:02.112 --> 00:56:04.698
Thought you might wanna have
a look at it.

386
00:56:36.730 --> 00:56:39.483
What was that?
I�s American artillery.

387
00:56:42.236 --> 00:56:44.029
Friendly fire.

388
00:56:44.112 --> 00:56:46.031
How many casualties?

389
00:56:48.283 --> 00:56:50.911
What the hell happened here. Joe?

390
00:56:55.582 --> 00:56:57.167
Hey. Joe.

391
00:56:58.919 --> 00:57:00.963
Colonel Moore!

392
00:57:03.382 --> 00:57:05.634
Colonel!
Colonel Moore!

393
00:57:08.679 --> 00:57:11.223
What is the key to your victory?
Sir. tell us how you feel.

394
00:57:11.306 --> 00:57:13.475
Do you feel the States
will be forced...

395
00:57:13.559 --> 00:57:15.519
to take the North Vietnamese
more seriously?

396
00:57:15.519 --> 00:57:18.522
How do you feel about
the loss ofyour men. sir?

397
00:57:18.605 --> 00:57:21.358
Have you notified
the families. sir?

398
00:58:36.600 --> 00:58:38.519
I'm glad you made it. son.

399
00:58:39.645 --> 00:58:41.980
Thankyou. sir.
You too.

400
00:58:46.860 --> 00:58:48.904
I'll never forgive myself.

401
00:58:51.281 --> 00:58:53.033
For what. sir?

402
00:58:58.038 --> 00:58:59.957
That my men...

403
00:59:03.794 --> 00:59:06.296
That my men died and I didn't.

404
00:59:28.569 --> 00:59:30.737
Sir. I don't...

405
00:59:30.821 --> 00:59:33.490
I don't know how to tell this story.

406
00:59:34.825 --> 00:59:37.119
Well. you got to. Joe.

407
00:59:38.996 --> 00:59:41.874
You tell the American people
what these men did here.

408
00:59:46.587 --> 00:59:48.839
You tell 'em how my troopers died.

409
00:59:55.470 --> 00:59:57.055
Yes. sir.

410
01:00:01.602 --> 01:00:03.228
Thank you.

411
01:00:51.276 --> 01:00:54.321
All of our men. living and dead.
are off the field. sir.

412
01:00:54.404 --> 01:00:56.323
Well done. Sergeant Major.

413
01:02:53.649 --> 01:02:56.818
In Saigon. Hal Moore's superiors
congratulated him...

414
01:02:56.902 --> 01:02:59.821
for killing over 1800
enemy soldiers.

415
01:03:01.114 --> 01:03:03.534
Then ordered him to lead
the men of the 7th Cavalry...

416
01:03:03.575 --> 01:03:05.994
back into the Valley of Death.

417
01:03:06.078 --> 01:03:07.955
He led them...

418
01:03:08.038 --> 01:03:10.165
and fought beside them...

419
01:03:10.207 --> 01:03:12.835
for 235 more days.

420
01:03:34.690 --> 01:03:37.609
Kids. go to bed.
Isn't there someone at the door?

421
01:03:37.693 --> 01:03:39.862
Go to bed!

422
01:04:20.110 --> 01:04:23.447
Children. your daddy's home!
Daddy!

423
01:04:29.453 --> 01:04:32.372
Some had families waiting.

424
01:04:32.456 --> 01:04:36.168
For others. their only family
would be the men they bled beside.

425
01:04:36.251 --> 01:04:40.172
There were no bands. no flags...

426
01:04:40.255 --> 01:04:42.841
no honor guards to welcome them home.

427
01:04:44.092 --> 01:04:47.596
They went to war because
their country ordered them to.

428
01:04:47.679 --> 01:04:50.682
But in the end they fought
not for their country or their flag.

429
01:04:52.142 --> 01:04:54.436
They fought for each other...

430
01:04:58.273 --> 01:04:59.983
Dear Barbara...

431
01:05:00.067 --> 01:05:05.072
I have no words to express to you
my sadness of the loss of Jack.

432
01:05:06.406 --> 01:05:08.909
The world is a lesser place
without him.

433
01:05:09.993 --> 01:05:12.663
But I know he is with God
and the angels.

434
01:05:12.746 --> 01:05:16.583
And even heaven is improved
by his presence there.

435
01:05:18.043 --> 01:05:20.170
I know you. too.
are sure of this...

436
01:05:20.254 --> 01:05:23.841
and yet this knowledge
can't diminish his loss...

437
01:05:23.924 --> 01:05:25.801
and your grief.

438
01:05:26.844 --> 01:05:30.138
With abiding respect and affection.
Hal Moore.

439
01:05:43.277 --> 01:05:45.445
We who have seen war...

440
01:05:45.529 --> 01:05:47.781
will never stop seeing it.

441
01:05:50.450 --> 01:05:54.246
In the silence of the night.
we will always hear the screams.

442
01:05:58.417 --> 01:06:00.669
So this is our story...

443
01:06:02.171 --> 01:06:04.882
for we were soldiers once...

444
01:06:04.965 --> 01:06:06.884
and young.
